name: Brent TERRY, Petitioner v. Honorable Judge Rosalyn K. ROBINSON, Respondent

parties: Brent TERRY, Petitioner v. Honorable Judge Rosalyn K. ROBINSON, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 31st day of July, 2013, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED, and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus is DENIED. The Prothonotary is directed to strike the name of the jurist from the caption.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

casebody.head_matter:
73 A.3d 522
Brent TERRY, Petitioner v. Honorable Judge Rosalyn K. ROBINSON, Respondent.
No. 69 EM 2013.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
July 31, 2013.
